x^p - y^p
|x^p -y^p|
|x-y|^p
0 < p <\infty
p
x,y>0
|x-y|^p\le p|x-y|(x^{p-1}+y^{p-1}), \text{ for }p\ge 1
x\ge y>0
|x-y|^p\le \frac{p}{2}x^{p-2}|x-y|(x^2+y^2), \text{ for }p\ge 2
x,y
2^{1-p}|x-y|^p\le\big|x|x|^{p-1}-y|y|^{p-1}\big|\le|x-y|(|x|^{p-1}+|y|^{p-1}), \text{ for }p\ge 1
|x|<M
y<M
|x^p-y^p|=|x-y||x^{p-1}+x^{p-2}y+\cdots+xy^{p-2}+y^{p-1}|
|x^p-y^p|<pM^{p-1}|x-y|
